## ✅ Coding Conventions

### TypeScript/React (Frontend)
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Use `@/` path alias for imports (e.g., `@/lib/firebase`)
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling (NO inline styles)
- Follow existing component patterns in `src/app/components/`
- Use Framer Motion for animations
- Client components must have `"use client"` directive

### Python (Backend)
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Use type hints for all functions
- Use async/await for I/O operations
- Follow existing patterns in `agents/` folder

### General
- Keep files focused and single-purpose
- Add meaningful comments for complex logic only
- Never delete existing comments unless asked
- Prefer editing existing files over creating new ones

